=== Bonus: investigation interaction (M4/M3 strategies re-run after the index landed) ===
POST /api/statement-runs?period=2025-03&strategy=NAIVE&limitAccounts=1000
  {"runId":5,"strategy":"NAIVE","accounts":1000,"statementsWritten":1000,"elapsedMs":6853,"statementsPerSec":145.92,"jdbcQueryCount":2003}
  -> same 2003 queries as the pre-index baseline (207,538ms) - query COUNT is
     unchanged (that's M4's variable), but each of the 1000 lazy per-account
     SELECTs now hits the index instead of a seq scan: 207.5s -> 6.85s (~30x).

POST /api/statement-runs?period=2025-03&strategy=FETCH_JOIN&limitAccounts=1000
  {"runId":6,"strategy":"FETCH_JOIN","accounts":667,"statementsWritten":667,"elapsedMs":2073,"statementsPerSec":321.76,"jdbcQueryCount":670}
  -> modest improvement (2486ms -> 2073ms): the fetch-join's single chunk
     query was already reading a bounded id range with the account_id FK's
     implicit index support before V3; the composite index mainly helps
     per-row point lookups (NAIVE's access pattern), less so a range scan
     that was already fairly targeted.
